The bank will announce measures of dealing with the consequences of the Russia- Ukraine conflict which has also affected the continent. Delegates will also look at the issue of food security. The African continent has been severely exposed to food insecurity as the conflict rages on between Russia and Ukraine. Some countries are looking at the African Development Bank Group to offer solutions. $1.5 billion has been allocated to deal with hunger as global supply of wheat, soya beans and maize has been affected due to global conflict. The gathering will be held as the continent is still dealing with the impact of climate change.  --SABC--